The paper discusses the current state and future directions of simultaneous localization and mapping (SLAM) technology, which is primarily used in robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics and Automation). The paper also discusses topics related to computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG), which are all relevant to SLAM. Additionally, the paper discusses theoretical performance guarantees and active SLAM, which are related to control systems (cs.SY).
